parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause sudden stops, loss of control, and accidents, while oil leaks can lead to engine damage and failure.
Broken motor mounts can cause the engine to rotate, leading to damage to surrounding components and potentially causing accidents.
Cracked or broken belts can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of power, leading to accidents or breakdowns.
Failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to fail to start, leading to inconvenience, delay, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Engine cranks but does not start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause damage, injury, or fatalities, and are a significant safety risk.
Failure of the EGR system can cause surging, bucking, and loss of power, leading to accidents or breakdowns.

The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially in heavy traffic conditions. In severe cases, it can also lead to electrical fires, posing a risk to the occupants and surrounding property.
symptoms: The engine stalls when the key is released
the vehicle stalls for no reason
the ignition switch catches on fire
the vehicle starts smoldering or catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to inadequate restraint during a collision, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not lock
the seat belt buckle releases unexpectedly
the button to release the seat belt is inoperative
the seat belt buckle is broken and will not latch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as well as damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly surges forward as if the accelerator pedal has been fully pressed
causing the vehicle to accelerate rapidly and potentially leading to loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling issue can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, and damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when shifting into drive
and/or when coming to a complete stop
requiring the driver to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine racing can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and damage to property, as well as potential engine damage.
symptoms: The engine races at very high RPM when started
